{
  "texts": [
    "Children with more exposure to and affinity with digital voice assistants have more pronounced psychological conceptions of technology, but it is unclear whether conceptions of technology and living things are blurred together (Festerling et al., 2022).",
    "Children do distinguish between technology and other living things through ascriptions of intelligence, however (Bernstein and Crowley, 2008).",
    "Goal-directed, autonomous behavior (a component of ToM) is one of the key mechanisms by which children distinguish an object as being alive (Opfer, 2002; Opfer and Siegler, 2004).",
    "Given that children appear to be ascribing mind to technology more than ever, this trend is likely to continue with AI advancement.",
    "We are skeptical that socially mistreating AI can result in emotional relief, translating into better social behavior toward other people."
  ]
}